[
  {
    "startTime": 0.0,
    "endTime": 7.2,
    "text": "[Music]"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 7.2,
    "endTime": 9.2,
    "text": "many of us will experience some kind of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 9.2,
    "endTime": 11.2,
    "text": "trauma during our lifetime"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 11.2,
    "endTime": 13.36,
    "text": "sometimes we escape with no long-term"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 13.36,
    "endTime": 14.24,
    "text": "effects"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 14.24,
    "endTime": 17.119,
    "text": "but for millions of us those experiences"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 17.119,
    "endTime": 17.92,
    "text": "linger"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 17.92,
    "endTime": 19.92,
    "text": "causing symptoms like flashbacks"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 19.92,
    "endTime": 21.68,
    "text": "nightmares and negative thoughts that"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 21.68,
    "endTime": 24.0,
    "text": "interfere with everyday life"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.0,
    "endTime": 26.24,
    "text": "this phenomenon called post-traumatic"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 26.24,
    "endTime": 28.72,
    "text": "stress disorder or ptsd"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 28.72,
    "endTime": 31.599,
    "text": "isn't a personal failing rather it's a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 31.599,
    "endTime": 33.28,
    "text": "treatable malfunction of certain"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 33.28,
    "endTime": 35.92,
    "text": "biological mechanisms that allow us to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 35.92,
    "endTime": 36.48,
    "text": "cope"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 36.48,
    "endTime": 40.0,
    "text": "with dangerous experiences to understand"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 40.0,
    "endTime": 40.96,
    "text": "ptsd"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 40.96,
    "endTime": 42.64,
    "text": "we first need to understand how the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.64,
    "endTime": 45.68,
    "text": "brain processes a wide range of ordeals"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 45.68,
    "endTime": 47.52,
    "text": "including the death of a loved one"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 47.52,
    "endTime": 49.12,
    "text": "domestic violence"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 49.12,
    "endTime": 52.64,
    "text": "injury or illness abuse rape"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 52.64,
    "endTime": 56.0,
    "text": "war car accidents and natural disasters"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 56.0,
    "endTime": 57.68,
    "text": "these events can bring on feelings of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.68,
    "endTime": 59.28,
    "text": "danger and helplessness"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 59.28,
    "endTime": 61.68,
    "text": "which activate the brain's alarm system"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 61.68,
    "endTime": 62.879,
    "text": "known as the fight"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 62.879,
    "endTime": 66.0,
    "text": "flight freeze response when this alarm"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 66.0,
    "endTime": 68.159,
    "text": "sounds the hypothalamic pituitary and"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 68.159,
    "endTime": 69.28,
    "text": "adrenal systems"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 69.28,
    "endTime": 72.24,
    "text": "known as the hpa axis work together to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 72.24,
    "endTime": 74.08,
    "text": "send signals to the autonomic"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 74.08,
    "endTime": 76.479,
    "text": "nervous system that's the network that"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 76.479,
    "endTime": 78.24,
    "text": "communicates with adrenal glands and"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 78.24,
    "endTime": 80.0,
    "text": "internal organs to help regulate"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 80.0,
    "endTime": 81.52,
    "text": "functions like heart rate"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 81.52,
    "endTime": 84.479,
    "text": "digestion and respiration these signals"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 84.479,
    "endTime": 86.32,
    "text": "start a chemical cascade"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 86.32,
    "endTime": 88.159,
    "text": "that floods the body with several"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 88.159,
    "endTime": 89.84,
    "text": "different stress hormones"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.84,
    "endTime": 91.84,
    "text": "causing physiological changes that"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 91.84,
    "endTime": 94.159,
    "text": "prepare the body to defend itself"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 94.159,
    "endTime": 96.079,
    "text": "our heart rate speeds up breathing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 96.079,
    "endTime": 98.88,
    "text": "quickens and muscles tense"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 98.88,
    "endTime": 101.36,
    "text": "even after a crisis is over escalated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 101.36,
    "endTime": 103.439,
    "text": "levels of stress hormones may last for"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 103.439,
    "endTime": 103.92,
    "text": "days"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 103.92,
    "endTime": 105.84,
    "text": "contributing to jittery feelings"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 105.84,
    "endTime": 108.0,
    "text": "nightmares and other symptoms"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 108.0,
    "endTime": 109.92,
    "text": "for most people these experiences"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 109.92,
    "endTime": 112.479,
    "text": "disappear within a few days to two weeks"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 112.479,
    "endTime": 114.96,
    "text": "as their hormone levels stabilize but a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 114.96,
    "endTime": 117.119,
    "text": "small percentage of those who experience"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 117.119,
    "endTime": 119.68,
    "text": "trauma have persistent problems"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 119.68,
    "endTime": 122.159,
    "text": "sometimes vanishing temporarily only to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 122.159,
    "endTime": 122.88,
    "text": "resurface"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 122.88,
    "endTime": 125.04,
    "text": "months later we don't completely"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 125.04,
    "endTime": 126.96,
    "text": "understand what's happening in the brain"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 126.96,
    "endTime": 128.64,
    "text": "but one theory is that the stress"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 128.64,
    "endTime": 130.0,
    "text": "hormone cortisol"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 130.0,
    "endTime": 132.4,
    "text": "may be continuously activating the fight"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 132.4,
    "endTime": 134.0,
    "text": "flight freeze response"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 134.0,
    "endTime": 136.48,
    "text": "while reducing overall brain functioning"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 136.48,
    "endTime": 139.28,
    "text": "leading to a number of negative symptoms"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 139.28,
    "endTime": 140.959,
    "text": "these symptoms often fall into four"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 140.959,
    "endTime": 143.04,
    "text": "categories intrusive thoughts"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 143.04,
    "endTime": 145.52,
    "text": "like dreams and flashbacks avoiding"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 145.52,
    "endTime": 147.12,
    "text": "reminders of the trauma"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 147.12,
    "endTime": 149.44,
    "text": "negative thoughts and feelings like fear"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 149.44,
    "endTime": 151.04,
    "text": "anger and guilt"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 151.04,
    "endTime": 153.599,
    "text": "and reactive symptoms like irritability"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 153.599,
    "endTime": 157.04,
    "text": "and difficulty sleeping not everyone has"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 157.04,
    "endTime": 159.12,
    "text": "all these symptoms or experiences them"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 159.12,
    "endTime": 161.519,
    "text": "to the same extent and intensity"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 161.519,
    "endTime": 163.44,
    "text": "when problems last more than a month"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 163.44,
    "endTime": 166.08,
    "text": "ptsd is often diagnosed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 166.08,
    "endTime": 169.2,
    "text": "genetics ongoing overwhelming stress"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 169.2,
    "endTime": 171.84,
    "text": "and many risk factors like pre-existing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 171.84,
    "endTime": 173.84,
    "text": "mental illnesses or lack of emotional"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 173.84,
    "endTime": 174.48,
    "text": "support"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 174.48,
    "endTime": 176.48,
    "text": "likely play a role in determining who"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 176.48,
    "endTime": 178.8,
    "text": "will experience ptsd"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 178.8,
    "endTime": 181.599,
    "text": "but the underlying cause is still a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 181.599,
    "endTime": 183.84,
    "text": "medical"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 183.84,
    "endTime": 186.959,
    "text": "a major challenge of coping with ptsd is"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 186.959,
    "endTime": 188.879,
    "text": "sensitivity to triggers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.879,
    "endTime": 190.959,
    "text": "physical and emotional stimuli that the"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 190.959,
    "endTime": 192.64,
    "text": "brain associates with the original"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 192.64,
    "endTime": 193.599,
    "text": "trauma"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 193.599,
    "endTime": 196.159,
    "text": "these can be everyday sensations that"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 196.159,
    "endTime": 197.68,
    "text": "aren't inherently dangerous"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 197.68,
    "endTime": 199.68,
    "text": "but prompt powerful physical and"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 199.68,
    "endTime": 201.519,
    "text": "emotional reactions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 201.519,
    "endTime": 204.08,
    "text": "for example the smell of a campfire"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 204.08,
    "endTime": 206.319,
    "text": "could evoke the memory of being trapped"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 206.319,
    "endTime": 209.76,
    "text": "in a burning house for someone with ptsd"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 209.76,
    "endTime": 211.519,
    "text": "that memory activates the same"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 211.519,
    "endTime": 213.92,
    "text": "neurochemical cascade as the original"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 213.92,
    "endTime": 214.879,
    "text": "event"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 214.879,
    "endTime": 217.04,
    "text": "that then stirs up the same feelings of"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 217.04,
    "endTime": 218.879,
    "text": "panic and helplessness"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 218.879,
    "endTime": 221.04,
    "text": "as if they're experiencing the trauma"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 221.04,
    "endTime": 223.28,
    "text": "all over again"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 223.28,
    "endTime": 225.36,
    "text": "trying to avoid these triggers which are"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 225.36,
    "endTime": 227.2,
    "text": "sometimes unpredictable"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 227.2,
    "endTime": 229.519,
    "text": "can lead to isolation that can leave"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 229.519,
    "endTime": 231.2,
    "text": "people feeling invalidated"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 231.2,
    "endTime": 233.92,
    "text": "ignored or misunderstood like a pause"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 233.92,
    "endTime": 235.599,
    "text": "button has been pushed on their lives"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 235.599,
    "endTime": 237.439,
    "text": "while the rest of the world continues"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 237.439,
    "endTime": 238.879,
    "text": "around them"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 238.879,
    "endTime": 241.76,
    "text": "but there are options if you think you"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 241.76,
    "endTime": 243.76,
    "text": "might be suffering from ptsd"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 243.76,
    "endTime": 245.84,
    "text": "the first step is an evaluation with a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 245.84,
    "endTime": 247.2,
    "text": "mental health professional"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 247.2,
    "endTime": 249.04,
    "text": "who can direct you towards the many"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 249.04,
    "endTime": 250.48,
    "text": "resources available"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 250.48,
    "endTime": 252.72,
    "text": "psychotherapy can be very effective for"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 252.72,
    "endTime": 253.76,
    "text": "ptsd"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 253.76,
    "endTime": 255.92,
    "text": "helping patients better understand their"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 255.92,
    "endTime": 256.799,
    "text": "triggers"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 256.799,
    "endTime": 258.4,
    "text": "and certain medications can make"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 258.4,
    "endTime": 260.0,
    "text": "symptoms more manageable"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 260.0,
    "endTime": 262.079,
    "text": "as can self-care practices like"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 262.079,
    "endTime": 264.96,
    "text": "mindfulness and regular exercise"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 264.96,
    "endTime": 267.12,
    "text": "what if you notice signs of ptsd in a"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 267.12,
    "endTime": 268.88,
    "text": "friend or family member"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 268.88,
    "endTime": 271.199,
    "text": "social support acceptance and empathy"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 271.199,
    "endTime": 273.28,
    "text": "are key to helping and recovery"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 273.28,
    "endTime": 274.88,
    "text": "let them know you believe their account"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 274.88,
    "endTime": 276.4,
    "text": "of what they're experiencing"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 276.4,
    "endTime": 277.919,
    "text": "and that you don't blame them for their"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 277.919,
    "endTime": 280.4,
    "text": "reactions if they're open to it"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 280.4,
    "endTime": 282.56,
    "text": "encourage them to seek evaluation and"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 282.56,
    "endTime": 283.759,
    "text": "treatment"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 283.759,
    "endTime": 286.32,
    "text": "ptsd has been called the hidden wound"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 286.32,
    "endTime": 287.759,
    "text": "because it comes without outward"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 287.759,
    "endTime": 289.12,
    "text": "physical signs"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 289.12,
    "endTime": 291.759,
    "text": "but even if it is an invisible disorder"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 291.759,
    "endTime": 294.96,
    "text": "it doesn't have to be a silent one"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 294.96,
    "endTime": 296.96,
    "text": "mental health conditions impact millions"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 296.96,
    "endTime": 298.4,
    "text": "of people around the world"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 298.4,
    "endTime": 300.88,
    "text": "yet are often misunderstood check out"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 300.88,
    "endTime": 311.84,
    "text": "this playlist to get informed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 312.32,
    "endTime": 314.4,
    "text": "you"
  }
]